in his sequel to William Woodruff (25 September) you state that &quot;in 1946 he resumed studies in economic history at Oxford and in 1950 won a Houblon-Norman fellowship...at the same time he was studying for a bachelor&#39;s degree, one master&#39;s degree and one doctorate.&quot;
