Industrial prices continue to rise
In the month of August 2008, the national industrial sale prices increased by 0.1 percent in comparison with the prices of the previous month and with 12.9 percent in comparison with the prices of the month of August 2007 - reported the Central Bureau of Statistics (KSH).
Industrial export prices rose 1.1 percent compared to July 2008 and decreased 3.9 percent compared to the previous year.
And as a result of changes in domestic and export prices, industrial producer prices increased 0.7 percent from the previous month and 3.2 percent from the previous year.
Industrial sales prices increased only minimally, with 0.1 percent.
Domestic sales prices of the processing industry sectors increased slightly, with 0.1 percent compared to the month of July.
The greatest increase in the magnitude of prices occurred in August 2008, in the leather and footwear production sector (2.8 percent), due first of all to the 4.6 percent monthly increase in prices. bags and belts and a 2.5 percent increase in footwear.
The higher price level of plastic and chemical base materials resulted in a significant monthly increase in the prices of the chemical materials production branch (1.6 percent).
There was a price decrease in the petrochemical sector (1.4 percent), in the production of electrical machines and instruments (0.9 percent), as well as - to a minimal extent - in the wood processing sectors (0.1 percent).
The prices of paper manufacturing, publishing and printing did not change.
In the rest of the sectors of the processing industry there was an increase in prices between 0.2 and 0.9 percent.
In the supply of electricity, gas, heat and water, which represent an important weight in internal trade, an increase of 0.3 percent was registered in the month of August, primarily as a result of the effect of the increase in prices official as of July 1st.
In a comparison of a period of twelve months - in the national sales of the sectors of the processing industry - the greatest increase in prices was registered in the petrochemical sector (32.4 percent).
In the metal manufacturing sector an increase of 13.2 percent was observed, while in the food, beverages and tobacco industry, of determining weight, there was an increase of 11 percent.
A decrease in prices was registered in the textile industry (2.5 percent), as well as in the manufacture of electrical machines and instruments (0.3 percent).
In the rest of the processing sectors, the growth rate of prices was between 0.6 and 9.1 percent.
During the past year in the processing industry globally prices increased with 10.2 percent.
The prices of electricity, gas supply, heat and water exceeded the prices of the previous year by 18.7 percent.
In the month of August, among the different sectors of domestic trade, the largest monthly increase in prices (0.7 percent) was registered in the investment goods sectors.
In the consumer goods sectors, prices increased by 0.3 percent, in the prices of the energy sector and of the intermediary sectors there were no changes with respect to the previous month.
In the month of August 2008, compared to the same month of the previous year, the highest price increase occurred in the energy sectors and in the intermediary industry (16.8 percent).
In the branches that produce consumer goods, a 6.8 percent decrease was registered, and in investment goods, 1.4 percent.
The industry&#39;s export prices calculated in HUF increased by 1.1 percent from the previous month, and compared to 12 months, there was a decrease of 3.9 percent.
The price of our national currency in one month fell 1.7 percent against the euro and 7.1 percent against the dollar, compared to August 2007 it strengthened 7.5 percent against against the euro and 15.9 percent against the dollar.
