What counts is to sensitize consumers and make this information public domain.
We must also re-examine existing control systems in light of this scientific opinion, so that they are broadly effective and keep pace with new technology.&quot;
Bruxel had asked the Independent Scientific Committee to examine the problem, noting the widespread use of portable music devices and the increase in the number of young people exposed to the noise that this causes.
&quot;Scientists - concludes the EU executive - confirm that it is cause for concern and the European Commission will now examine together with the member states and interested parties what measures could possibly be adopted to better protect children and adolescents from noise exposure from portable music and related devices&quot;.
