In its opinion, the Ue Scientific Committee notes that if users of portable musical devices listen to music at high volume (more than 89 decibels) for only 5 hours a week, they exceed the limit currently in force regarding the maximum noise allowed in the post. of work.
Those who listen to music in such conditions for longer periods risk permanent hearing loss after a period of 5 years.
