So whoever finds himself a sovereign certainly has many more cards than whoever is not, and who has the misfortune of living in a position without crops, without oil and without water.
I come to the second novelty that presages a fracture.
Who says Territory, State, Government, inevitably says Politics and Leadership.
In this sense, the economic crisis seems to produce two convergent phenomena.
On the one hand, the objective awareness of the need for leadership, the request of someone who knows how to take the situation in hand.
On the other hand, a wave of discredit for the existing leadership, of an inadequate economic species revealed with many dark areas.
And together something deeper and in a certain sense disturbing: a discredit, an intolerance, an inadequate image, a sense of remoteness, which tends to involve the entire ruling class of the Western countries in increasing numbers.
It seems to advance more and more, in various parts of the population, the conviction that before their actions are the same as those of the social elites up to now, the same way of feeling and being, their culture in the comprehensive exception of the term , to have done his own time and to be stranger to the opinions of the majority.
